Package: glmOJ
Title: Toolkit for Count Regression Modeling
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Oscar", "Jaroker", , "ojaroker@colgate.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides a workflow for fitting, diagnosing, and interpreting
    count regression models. Supports Poisson, negative binomial, zero-inflated
    Poisson, and zero-inflated negative binomial models. Includes data
    summarization tools, randomized quantile residual diagnostics, and a
    general-purpose wrapper that fits all four model families and selects the
    best by AIC.
License: `use_mit_license()`, `use_gpl3_license()` or friends to pick a
    license
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
URL: https://github.com/ojaroker/glmOJ, http://oscar.jaroker.com/glmOJ/
BugReports: https://github.com/ojaroker/glmOJ/issues
